# Spark Systems — Cafe POS

## Core System

- Productized POS system for cafes/restaurants
- Fast, touch-first interface
- Minimal customization
- Single-tenant now, multi-tenant later

---

## Stack

### Backend
- Laravel (monolith)
- Session-based authentication (Laravel Breeze)
- Web routes for app
- API routes only for testing/integrations

### Frontend
- Vue 3 (Composition API)
- Vite
- PrimeVue + Tailwind
- SPA mounted inside Blade

---

## Roles

- admin
- accounting
- waiter

Use spatie/laravel-permission

- Treat user as having one role
- Always use `$user->roles`
- Do not define custom role relations

---

## Core Models

### UnitGroup
- id
- name
- position
- is_active

### Unit
- id
- unit_group_id
- name
- capacity
- is_active
- is_available
- current_order_id (nullable, no FK required)
- position

### Order
- id
- unit_id
- user_id
- status (open, closed, cancelled)
- total
- opened_at
- closed_at

### OrderItem
- id
- order_id
- product_id (nullable)
- name (snapshot)
- price (snapshot)
- quantity
- total
- type (product, service, timer)
- notes (nullable)
- meta (json)

### Product
- id
- name
- description
- type (physical, service_fixed, service_timer)
- price
- price_per_hour
- is_available
- is_limited
- stock_quantity

### TimerSession
- id
- unit_id
- order_id
- product_id
- started_at
- ended_at
- duration_minutes
- calculated_total

### Expense
- id
- title
- amount
- spent_at
- notes
- user_id

### Setting
- id
- key
- value

### Media
- use spatie/laravel-medialibrary

---

## Core Logic

- Unit holds current active order via `current_order_id`
- Order is the main entity
- OrderItem stores final billing data (snapshot)
- TimerSession tracks time only, not billing
- On timer stop → create OrderItem

---

## Translations

- Use polymorphic `translations` table
- Fields:
  - locale
  - key
  - value
  - translatable_type
  - translatable_id

- Always keep fallback value in main table

---

## Backend Rules

- Keep controllers thin
- Use Eloquent relationships
- Use helper methods for logic (e.g. isFree, isBusy)
- Avoid complex queries in POS flow
- Avoid unnecessary foreign keys during early development
